od.oracle.apps.xxom.atp
Class ATPProcessControl

java.lang.Object
  od.oracle.apps.xxom.atp.ATPProcessControl

public class ATPProcessControl
extends java.lang.Object

This is the standard API to be used to call the Custom ATP with the required parameters. Calling Application would invoke the object of this class to get the necessary ATP details.

Constructor to be invoked with arrays of parameter values. In case the inquiry is for a multiple items eg: during a search or for rescheduling an entire order this Constructor can be Invoked for. This invokes the process control and spawns individual threads for each order line. Currently not implemented - waiting on business decision on how Ship Sets would be handled.

Parameters:
internal_item_number - Array of Item Number of the product being inquired
item_Quantity - Array of Quantity requested in the inquiry
Quantity_UOM - Array of Quantity UOM of the item
Customer_Number - Array of Customer Number of the customer requesting the item
Cust_Shipto_Loc - Array of Customer Ship to Location if specified
Shipto_Loc_Postal_Code - Array of Customer zip code specified
Current_Date - Array of Current Date and Time
Req_Date - Array of Requested date and time
Req_Date_Type - Array of Request date type
ATP_Call_Type - Array of ATP call type
timezone_code - Array of Customer time zone code
Order_Cateory - Array of Order category
Order_type - Array of Order Type
Unit_Selling_Price - Array of Unit selling price of the item
Currency - Array of Currency of the customer
Operating_Unit - Array of Operating Unit of this Call
Ship_Method - Array of Ship Method desired
ShipFrom_Org - Array of Ship from org if specified
Order_Number - Array of Order Number if for ReScheduling
Order_Line_Number - Array of Order Line Number if for ReScheduling

Constructor to be invoked with element parameter values and not Arrays. The constructor invokes the process control for handling one line inquiry ONLY. Necessary objects such as the validation object, Connetion Pool manager object and PreProcess objects are invoked.

Parameters:
internal_item_number - Item Number of the product being inquired
item_Quantity - Quantity requested in the inquiry
Quantity_UOM - Quantity UOM of the item
Customer_Number - Customer Number of the customer requesting the item
Cust_Shipto_Loc - Customer Ship to Location if specified
Shipto_Loc_Postal_Code - Customer zip code specified
Current_Date - Current Date and Time
Req_Date - Requested date and time
Req_Date_Type - Request date type
ATP_Call_Type - ATP call type
timezone_code - Customer time zone code
Unit_Selling_Price - Unit selling price of the item
Currency - Currency of the customer
Operating_Unit - Operating Unit of this Call
Ship_Method - Ship Method desired
ShipFrom_Org - Ship from org if specified
Order_Number - Order Number if for ReScheduling
Order_Line_Number - Order Line Number if for ReScheduling
